text: Stunning Upgraded Townhome in Highly Sought-After Grapevine Community-beautifully maintained & extensively upgraded townhome offering a perfect blend of style, comfort, & convenience. Nestled in desirable Grapevine, this home is move-in ready with nice updates & thoughtful touches throughout. Upon entering, youll be greeted by rich hardwood flooring that flows seamlessly through the main living spaces, complemented by fresh neutral paint tones & elegant crown molding. Large windows allow natural light to fill the home, creating a bright and welcoming ambiance. The heart of the home is the chef-inspired kitchen, designed for function & style with ample cabinetry, expansive counter space, & an open layout, perfect for cooking enthusiasts. Adjacent to the kitchen, the spacious dining and living areas provide an ideal setting for family gatherings or quiet evenings at home. A standout feature is the custom staircase with wrought iron railings, adding a touch of sophistication as you transition to the upper level. Step outside to your private backyard oasis with a pergola-covered patio (added in November 2020) and lushly landscaped greenspace. The fenced-in area provides privacy, making it an ideal retreat for morning coffee, outdoor dining, or unwinding after a long day. Recent Upgrades and Key Features Include: New Roof, Gutters & Window Screens (2023), New Exterior AC Unit & Coil (2022), New Furnace Damper Control Board & Motors (November 2024), New Garbage Disposal (2024), 125-250V EV Plug Installed in Garage Perfect for Electric Vehicle Charging The community offers well-maintained common greenspaces & a sparkling pool. Situated in the vibrant city of Grapevine, this home offers easy access to shopping, dining, entertainment, & major highways. Minutes from Historic Downtown Grapevine, DFW International Airport, & Grapevine Lake, making it an exceptional choice for commuters & those seeking an active lifestyle. Dont miss this rare opportunity!

text: 2905 Crestline Drive is a stunning, fully renovated 3+ BR home nestled in beautiful Woodland Hills, one of the most idyllic and sought-after neighborhoods in Grapevine. text: Step into luxury living with this V Patrick Gray Custom Home, thoughtfully designed as the builders personal residence. This space is perfect for year-round enjoyment, whether hosting summer BBQs or relaxing under the stars. Upstairs, discover three spacious ensuite bedrooms, each offering privacy and comfort, along with a versatile loft area that can serve as a playroom, study nook, or cozy lounge. This home is a perfect blend of luxury, thoughtful design, and superior craftsmanship. Schedule your private tour of 3300 Jackson Ct today and experience the ultimate in North Texas living.

920 Meadowbrook Dr is a 3 bedroom 2 bathroom remodeled house with an additional 1440 square foot shop sitting on over a third of an acre backing up to a creek just a half mile walk to Historic Grapevine Main St and next to Lake Grapevine. Inside the home brand new luxury vinyl planking, luxury window, door, trim, fixtures, and lighting package. Upgrades also include a new roof, water heater, HVAC, Electrical, hardware, cabinets, vanities, bathrooms, and a quartz on quartz kitchen with professionally designed bathrooms. Professional masonry fireplace. No feature has been overlooked on this beautiful home and of the most unique features in the city is a 30 by 48ft shop designed by the previous home owner who was an engineer. The shop is a business owner or car collectors dream with an overhead garage door, separate door, electric, and a walk in bathroom with a double vanity and storage. Shop has a thick concrete slab and 15ft deep pier foundation. No HOA. Brand new fence around the whole property with a custom steel gate to drive in the backyard. There is a gate in back to walk down to the creek. Owner is agent. Check out all the photos as the updates are amazing.

text: Move-in ready home ! Completely renovated. 3 bed, 2 bath, 2 car garage, In-unit Laundry. Located in the heart of Grapevine! Major system upgrades include brand-new HVAC, water heater, roof, electrical panel, and plumbing system, both bathrooms, kitchen, and laundry room. The garage itself is brand new. It is also equipped with a newly installed garage door motor, two remotes, a keypad entry, and a battery backup. Plus, new insulation has been added to the attic, enhancing energy efficiency. Foundation repairs have been completed, and the warranty is lifetime transferable. A hydrostatic test was performed to ensure the plumbing system is in good working condition. Situated on a private lot with no back neighbors. Step inside to find a fully renovated interior with fresh paint, new carpet, new luxury vinyl plank flooring, and an open-concept design ideal for entertaining. The kitchen has granite countertops, white shaker cabinets, stainless steel appliances, and a stylish subway tile backsplash. text: Enjoy the perfect blend of convenience and charm in this 4-bed, 3-bath home on a spacious .36-acre lot near Lake Grapevine. With flexible living spaces, including two large living areas and bedrooms both upstairs and down, theres plenty of room to grow. The oversized second-story bedroom is a private retreat with room for a sitting area or home office or workout space. French doors lead from the adjacent living area to a large deck with sweeping views and plenty of space for hosting friends, morning coffee or quiet evenings. Love to play outdoors? Head back downstairs and step outside to your backyard oasis. Here youll find a large diving pool, an expansive patio recently updated with durable rubberized flooring and loads of space to entertain. Or go exploring on the nearby hiking and biking trails at Lake Grapevine. The home's convenient location has you minutes from historic downtown Grapevine, DFW Airport, and upscale shopping and dining options in Southlake. Additional updates include fresh exterior paint, newly landscaped yard with irrigation, newer roof and HVAC systems. Come see it for yourself! ASSUMABLE VA LOAN

text: Great Location! Sought after award winning Grapevine-Colleyville ISD! text: Charming, clean, and move-in ready best describes this Craftsman style 3 bedroom 2.5 bath home! The current owners have invested in numerous upgrades, evident in the impeccable condition of this delightful well established neighborhood located in prime Historic Wall Street Township. This home was built by Maykus Custom home in the heart of downtown Grapevine only a few blocks away from Main Street. This cottage style of home preserves every aspect of being labeled Historic, from design, style, size and appeal with the advantage of being built only 7 years ago. Fully open concept living with hardwood solid red oak flooring, corner molding, door trim details and base board trim not to mention custom cabinetry, upgraded appliances and fixtures. Kitchen has upgraded quartz countertops with amazing canister lighting and stainless appliances with beverage cooler. This home has a 3 bed, 2.5 bath, study, 1st floor master and upstairs game room with two additional bedrooms. Living room has built-in surround sound in wall speakers. Master suite is split from the other rooms, master bath has separate shower, garden tub & a large walk-in closet. Downstairs office has built in cabinets. Separate utility room supports oversized appliances. Attic is full encapsulation on underside of roof with radiant barrier for reduced utility costs. Relax on the private back patio while enjoying the conveniences of the surrounding Grapevine amenities! Two car garage detached with epoxy flooring, artificial back yard grass, driveway gate and outdoor back patio. See list of upgrades, utilities fees and all other documents loaded in transaction file.

text: Welcome to the GE Hurst Historical House originally built in 1910. This home was extensively renovated and added on to in 2018 and is the essence of Grapevine historic living. It is situated on .54 acres with many native trees and a 960 sq ft garage workshop that has the look of an original barn. The house has over 4560 sq ft under roof and 2780 sq ft of living space. Many of the original features and trim work were preserved while fully updating the complete house and structure with all the modern top amenities. The renovated structure was rebuilt on top of a steel pier and beam foundation. The primary bedroom and guest suit along with the primary living areas are all located downstairs, while the upstairs has two additional bedrooms with full baths, a living area, and unique spacious office. The home has a porte-cochere near the mud room and laundry for easy entrance. Seller is a relative of listing agent.

We invite you to come and see this stunning property for yourself. Welcome home!
